{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:psalms.82",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 82,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 82 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:1",
      "text": "A canticle of a psalm for Asaph.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:2",
      "text": "O God, who shall be like to thee? hold not thy peace, neither be thou still, O God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:3",
      "text": "For lo, thy enemies have made a noise: and they that hate thee have lifted up the head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:4",
      "text": "They have taken a malicious counsel against thy people, and have consulted against thy saints.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:5",
      "text": "They have said: Come and let us destroy them, so that they be not a nation: and let the name of Israel be remembered no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:6",
      "text": "For they have contrived with one consent: they have made a covenant together against thee,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:7",
      "text": "The tabernacle of the Edomites, and the Ishmahelites: Moab, and the Agarens,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:8",
      "text": "Gebal, and Ammon and Amalec: the Philistines, with the inhabitants of Tyre.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:9",
      "text": "Yea, and the Assyrian also is joined with them: they are come to the aid of the sons of Lot.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:10",
      "text": "Do to them as thou didst to Madian and to Sisara: as to Jabin at the brook of Cisson.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:11",
      "text": "Who perished at Endor: and became as dung for the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:12",
      "text": "Make their princes like Oreb, and Zeb, and Zebee, and Salmana. All their princes,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:13",
      "text": "Who have said: Let us possess the sanctuary of God for an inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:14",
      "text": "O my God, make them like a wheel; and as stubble before the wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:15",
      "text": "As fire which burneth the wood: and as a flame burning mountains:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:16",
      "text": "So shalt thou pursue them with thy tempest: and shalt trouble them in thy wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:17",
      "text": "Fill their faces with shame; and they shall seek thy name, O Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:18",
      "text": "Let them be ashamed and troubled for ever and ever: and let them be confounded and perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.82.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 82,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 82:19",
      "text": "And let them know that the Lord is thy name: thou alone art the most High over all the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
